{
  "texts": [
    "For a given dataset size |D|, we fix all training hyperparameters (e.g., β = 0.1 and a learning rate of 5e-7) and only vary the number of training steps.",
    "We then repeat this process for |D| = {1, 10, 100} × 10 3, all randomly sampled from the dataset in Table 2.",
    "For other training details, please refer to Appendix A.2.",
    "We present the results in Figure 1.",
    "In Figure 1, we find that 1) under a fixed dataset size, performance quickly saturates/over-optimizes as training step increases (Rafailov et al., 2024; Gao et al., 2022); and 2) increasing dataset size raises the point of saturation."
  ]
}